cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.SE 

The paper deals with the verification of parametric Markov decision processes, which is a problem in the intersection of several subfields of computer science. The most relevant sub-category is likely cs.SY (Systems and Control), as the paper deals with decision-making in stochastic systems. Additionally, the paper uses optimization techniques, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with computational complexity, which could place it under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses applications of its approach to model repair and parameter synthesis, which suggests a connection to cs.SE (Software Engineering).
